The paper deals with binary search trees and their connection to subsets of points on the plane, which are topics typically studied in the computer science subfields of data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses the cost of search operations, which is a common topic in the subfield of algorithm analysis and design (cs.DM). The paper includes conjectures and proofs, which are common in the subfield of graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper discusses an access lemma, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT).
